emulib.plugins.memory

Class AbstractMemory

  • java.lang.Object
    • emulib.plugins.memory.AbstractMemory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Memory, Plugin

    public abstract class AbstractMemory
extends Object
implements Memory
    Abstract memory. It implements some fundamental methods which are usually shared across the most of memories.

      • setProgramStart

        public void setProgramStart(int address)
        Set program starting address (memory location). Mostly it is called by the emuStudio after the compiler returns. When the compiler compiles the source, the emuStudio gets compiled program starting address (if unknown, it will be 0) and pass it here.
        Specified by:
        setProgramStart in interface Memory
        Parameters:
        address - program starting address (memory location)
